❣️ Twelve years ago today I hit publish on my very first blog post. I don’t remember what it said and it's long gone by now (probably a good thing, ha.) I don't think I even realized it was Valentine's Day when I wrote it, as I was holding my baby boy on my lap and the remnants of postpartum depression on my shoulders. ⁠
⁠
The fact that I was creating something and putting it out into the world, was scary and thrilling and cathartic. I look back at that young mom who was just desperate enough to try something and I'm proud. I'm proud that she felt the fear and did it anyways. I'm proud that she kept going even when it was hard and embarrassing. And I'm thankful for the sweet reminder that love is what pushed her forward. ⁠
⁠
All that to say- Happy Valentine's Day to you! Instead of chocolates I'm giving you the gift of this drop-dead-gorgeous bathroom. You're welcome. 🥰 😘⁠
⁠
Design•⁠ @ambermcculloughdesign 
Photography•⁠ @emilyhartphoto

Ahhh still in love with this home and the images we created! We have a few more days shooting and I can’t wait to be back!

Get your gear on!! 📷️ ✨ I get so many questions about choosing the right gear for interior photography, so I broke it down for you in my latest blog post. From the camera I use, to the lenses I count on at every shoot, I've rounded it all up in one spot. The interior photography specialty can be confusing when you're first starting, but I'm here to help you every step of the way! Visit the link in my bio to read my blog and let me know what you think!⁠

✨✨Update: The surgery was successful and she is HOME recovering!! We are still waiting to hear back on what kind of tumor we are dealing with, but are SO relieved and thankful that the amazing neurosurgery team at OU Med was able to get all of it. It feels miraculous that she is home recovering 24 hours after brain surgery!!!
Friends, I wish I could describe what your comments and messages meant to us as we waited. Because I can’t find the words, I’ll use the words from the poem “Footprints”: 

The Lord replied, “My precious child, I love you and would never leave you. During your times of trial and suffering, when you see only one set of footprints, it was then that I carried you.” 👣

Thank you with all my heart!! ✨✨

Friends, this is a personal post for someone who is very dear to me. My sister, Jenny, will be undergoing brain surgery this morning to remove a large tumor. If you’re the praying type, will you lift her and her beautiful family up in prayer? She has dedicated her life to serving others and it’s our turn to take care of her. 
Thank you for all the prayers and positive thoughts! 🙏🏻✨

✨Update on my sister✨
We are in for a fight, and we are ready! 
This is my big sister, Jenny. You might recognize this photo from a recent “Knock Out Cancer” campaign at the Oklahoma Proton Center, where she is Vice President. 

Jenny started her career as a radiation therapist and has devoted her life to helping others defeat cancer. 

I had a proud sister moment a few months ago when I saw this photo larger than life on a billboard in OKC. Little did I, or any of us know that this fight would soon become a reality. 

Jenny had a large tumor removed from her brain one week ago. We found out a few days later that it is glioblastoma- an aggressive form of brain cancer. 

So many of you reached out with messages, comments, prayers, and support last week during her surgery. I can’t tell you just how much each of those meant to our family!!
Will you keep the prayers coming? We are full of faith and know that prayer can move mountains! 

I’m also linking in my bio a Go Fund Me that was set up on her behalf. Her family needs all the love and support you can give!! 
On behalf of Jenny, thank you so very much! 🙏🏻

Help me choose! Which shot catches your eye the most? ⁠

✨Sharing one of my favorite interior photography tips today!✨⁠
⁠
Reflections! I love using mirrors to tell the story of a room. Swipe to see the before of this image! ⁠
When setting up the shot I could see the reflection of the eye-catching kitchen light fixture in the mirror, but couldn't get *just* the right angle to convey it in the image. ⁠
Since I knew it was a real life moment, I decided to use some @photoshop magic to make it happen in the the finished image.🪄⁠
⁠
Want to learn how to do this and gain confidence as an interior photographer? Head to the mentoring page on my website (link in bio) to book a mentoring session with me. I'm so very passionate about helping you succeed!⁠
⁠
